                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13884560" author="rskvazh" created="Tue, 28 Jan 2014 20:29:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Does this linked with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6333&quot; title=&quot;ArrayIndexOutOfBound when using count(*) with over 10,000 rows&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-6333&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-6333&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13884725" author="mishail" created="Tue, 28 Jan 2014 21:34:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Restoring my original comment &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like &lt;tt&gt;remove&lt;/tt&gt; at &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.cassandra.db.ArrayBackedSortedColumns.ReverseSortedCollection.iterator&lt;/tt&gt; should use &lt;em&gt;idx&lt;/em&gt; (current item) instead of &lt;em&gt;idx--&lt;/em&gt; (next item)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Current implementation which throws ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;ReverseSortedCollection &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; AbstractCollection&amp;lt;Column&amp;gt;
    {
..........
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Iterator&amp;lt;Column&amp;gt;()
            {
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; idx = size() - 1;

                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt; hasNext()
                {
                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; idx &amp;gt;= 0;
                }

                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; Column next()
                {
                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; columns.get(idx--);
                }

                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void remove()
                {
                    columns.remove(idx--);
                }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13884743" author="rskvazh" created="Tue, 28 Jan 2014 21:56:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Does this fix (idx--) solve problem with read repair?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13884775" author="rskvazh" created="Tue, 28 Jan 2014 22:14:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wow. It seems &quot;nodetool scrub&quot; on node with odd row helped to me. Read repair restore that 32-nd row on other replicas, this CQL query worked properly and without exception now...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13884885" author="mishail" created="Tue, 28 Jan 2014 23:14:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for the problem plus unit-tests to reproduce (without fix)/ validate (with fix)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13884982" author="iamaleksey" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2014 04:20:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wouldn&apos;t it be simpler to just alter remove() to return columns.remove(idx + 1) ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13884990" author="mishail" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2014 04:30:50 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Wouldn&apos;t it be simpler to just alter remove() to return columns.remove(idx + 1) ?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this case you&apos;ll be able to call &lt;tt&gt;remove&lt;/tt&gt; arbitrary number of times, without calling &lt;tt&gt;next&lt;/tt&gt; at all, which breaks the Iterator&apos;s contract. &lt;br/&gt;
But yes, that will fix the original problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13885015" author="iamaleksey" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2014 05:19:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;All right. I don&apos;t like the two indexes though. Can we just get away with a &apos;nextCalled&apos; boolean? set it to true in next(), set it back to false in remove()?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That, and I&apos;d rather we just threw IllegalStateException with no message, like the stdlib iterators do (w/ no need for Preconditions). The last one is a nit/taste thing, feel free to ignore.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13885022" author="iamaleksey" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2014 05:27:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh, and 1.2 looks affected as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13885026" author="mishail" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2014 05:39:25 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Can we just get away with a &apos;nextCalled&apos; boolean? set it to true in next(), set it back to false in remove()?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Totally makes sense.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;That, and I&apos;d rather we just threw IllegalStateException with no message, like the stdlib iterators do (w/ no need for Preconditions)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adjusted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;v2 of the patch (for 2.0.x) attached.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13885028" author="iamaleksey" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2014 05:44:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM, go ahead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;nit: missing spaces around &apos;+&apos;, and I&apos;d rather just see IllegalStateException() there w/ null message - it&apos;s not like there can be several reasons for an exception here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13885037" author="mishail" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2014 05:59:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached the patch for 1.2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13885042" author="mishail" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2014 06:05:51 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;nit: missing spaces around &apos;+&apos;, and I&apos;d rather just see IllegalStateException() there w/ null message - it&apos;s not like there can be several reasons for an exception here.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adjusted in both patches&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13885055" author="iamaleksey" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2014 06:21:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13885183" author="rskvazh" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2014 09:53:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Guys, what about scrub and read repair problem?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13885853" author="iamaleksey" created="Wed, 29 Jan 2014 21:43:47 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Guys, what about scrub and read repair problem?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do you still have a problem?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
